LayoutNode.Content: Guangzhou Automobile Industry Group Co Ltd is a joint stock holding company that owns several Chinese automakers. A state-owned enterprise, it is also known as GAIG (Chinese: 广州汽车).
LayoutNode.SRC: Guangzhou Automobile Industry Group Co Ltd is a joint stock holding company that owns several Chinese automakers. A state-owned enterprise, it is also known as GAIG (Chinese: 广州汽车).

LayoutNode.Content: A Chinese partner of Japanese companies Toyota and Honda, GAIG owns Chinese production bases that churn out Chinese-market versions of the Japanese carmakers' models, which sell well in Southern China as of 2010.
LayoutNode.SRC: A Chinese partner of Japanese companies Toyota and Honda, GAIG owns Chinese production bases that churn out Chinese-market versions of the Japanese carmakers' models, which sell well in Southern China as of 2010.

LayoutNode.Content: It may have a joint venture with Johnson Controls, which should have started production in 2010 although the latter company's Chinese partner may be Guangzhou Automobile Group instead.
LayoutNode.SRC: It may have a joint venture with Johnson Controls, which should have started production in 2010 although the latter company's Chinese partner may be Guangzhou Automobile Group instead.

LayoutNode.Content: It subsidiary companies managed to manufacture more than 650,600 units in 2011 placing the company as the 6th most-productive on the domestic market.
LayoutNode.SRC: It subsidiary companies managed to manufacture more than 650,600 units in 2011 placing the company as the 6th most-productive on the domestic market.

LayoutNode.Content: Born during a reconstruction of the Guangzhou automotive industry in 2000, GAIG receives considerable support from the governments of Guangdong province and Guangzhou city.
LayoutNode.SRC: Born during a reconstruction of the Guangzhou automotive industry in 2000, GAIG receives considerable support from the governments of Guangdong province and Guangzhou city.

LayoutNode.Content: Formerly the Guangzhou Automobile Industry Group Company, it was renamed in 2005.
LayoutNode.SRC: Formerly the Guangzhou Automobile Industry Group Company, it was renamed in 2005.

LayoutNode.Content: Cars selling under the first car brand exclusive to GAIG, Trumpchi, went on offer in 2011. The sole model is a sedan. The car went on sale in 2011, but the first six months of sales disappointed.
LayoutNode.SRC: Cars selling under the first car brand exclusive to GAIG, Trumpchi, went on offer in 2011. The sole model is a sedan. The car went on sale in 2011, but the first six months of sales disappointed.

LayoutNode.Content: A Trumpchi-branded SUV will be added to the model line in April 2012.
LayoutNode.SRC: A Trumpchi-branded SUV will be added to the model line in April 2012.

LayoutNode.Content: In 2007 GAIG began putting in motion plans to sell automobiles under its own brand and to further this goal had acquired a controlling share in an R&D center at South China University of Technology. The goal of self-branded sales was also brought up on the company's website in 2010.
LayoutNode.SRC: In 2007 GAIG began putting in motion plans to sell automobiles under its own brand and to further this goal had acquired a controlling share in an R&D center at South China University of Technology. The goal of self-branded sales was also brought up on the company's website in 2010.

LayoutNode.Content: The Chinese State may have been an early driving force behind GAIG own-brand efforts.
LayoutNode.SRC: The Chinese State may have been an early driving force behind GAIG own-brand efforts.

LayoutNode.Content: Guangzhou Automobile Group Co Ltd (SEHK: 2238) was founded in 1997, and by 2005 it had become a holding of GAIG. As of 2009 it is the 6th largest automaker in China.
